children.subject: Please note: This position is for 7 months (covers spring and summer semesters).

It is preferred that the candidate is currently pursuing a Bachelor's degree in CS, EECS, or related field of study, and be able to work for at least 7 months for positions starting in January 2021. Candidate should be proficient in Python and C, and be familiar with Linux OS/drivers/kernel. I can send you more specific details about the available opportunities if you contact me via email. Thanks.
Are there any criteria such as age or experience with certain programs that this internship is looking for?

As far as I know (my current internship is virtual), Intel is currently operating on a Work From Home basis until June 2021. Therefore, it is likely that your internship will be fully virtual and you will be able to work at home (Intel will ship you the necessary materials to set up your home office).

It is preferred that the candidate is currently pursuing a Bachelor's degree in CS, EECS, or related field of study, and be able to work for at least 7 months for positions starting in January 2021. Candidate should be proficient in Python and C, and be familiar with Linux OS/drivers/kernel. I can send you more specific details about the available opportunities if you contact me via email. Thanks.
To clarify, a CS Minor does not qualify?

history.content: Applications for this opportunity are now closed.
history.subject: Intel Corporation Internship Opportunity

history.content:
Hi all!

I'm currently working as an intern at Intel and can help refer you to work as an intern in our department with positions starting in January 2021. You will need to return to school after the conclusion of this internship. Feel free to email me (howardho2021@berkeley.edu) if you're interested and I will send you available job posting details. Thanks!

Update 1: Openings only for students majoring in CS, EECS, or related field of study. Please send your resume so that I can refer you to the hiring manager.
Update 2: This position is for U.S. Workers only. You must be a U.S. citizen or U.S. Lawful Permanent Resident to be considered for this position. Intel will not sponsor a foreign national for this position.

UPDATE 3: I have received many applications for this opportunity, so the job postings are temporarily closed for new applicants.
